HEADWORD: Hydraulicon
<hw>Hy*drau"li*con</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Hydraulic</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>An ancient musical
instrument played by the action of water; a water organ.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>hydraulis</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

